item.title: Finding a good source
item.dc:creator: @Scape-JAVA Scape-JAVA
item.description:
@Scape-JAVA wrote:

[quote=“fuzzout, post:4, topic:548060”][quote author=Scape-JAVA link=topic=666965.msg4459845#msg4459845 date=1416979588]

You may need to elaborate what you mean.

A good source is just a starting point… you shouldn’t look for a source that nobody uses; rather you should get a barebones source and add/write your own things based on that template; creating your own content and distinguishing the server.

Good sources:
Deltascape
PI

no.
[/quote]

I see what you did there, and I agree… But I was just trying to be helpful.[/quote]

Project insanity is detrimental to ones ability when learning to program.
